NAME
	tk-notes (tk-display) - build entry/button/listbox Tk widgets, append entry text as lines to a notes file, and mirror that file into the listbox

INTERFACE
	tk-display (MatrixTkDisplay - Tk-hosted; init receives a Tk
	toplevel and widget prefix instead of a Draw display)

READS
	notes	whole file, one note per line; re-read each update tick
		with change detection

WRITES
	notes	appends "<text>\n" by whole-file read-modify-write
		(not atomic)

DESCRIPTION
	Enter or the Add button appends the entry text and refreshes the
	listbox.  Notes written externally (by an agent or `echo` from
	sh) appear on the next update tick, making the file a two-way
	channel between the pane and anything else in the namespace.
	Creates the mount directory at init if missing.
